<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="3.1_Various_period_of_occupation_structural_changes">3.1 Various period of occupation structural changes</span></h2>
<p>Base on the occupation classification, we have plotted figure 3-1 and 3-2 of the distribution of the parents' occupation over time for the two schools. After the establishment of New China, there is large structural change in the parents' occupation. The most significant change is that previously it is unlikely for children of farmers and workers to enter university. But later the come in large number, and even become the majority source of students at one time. This is a important realization of the Silent Revolution.</p>
